<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 07 at 12:22PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...WINTRY MIX TRANSITIONING TO LIGHT SNOW THIS AFTERNOON...
WEATHER...
* Leading edge of precipitation has started moving into the
region and will increase in coverage between now and 2 PM.
* Expect a wintry mix of sleet, snow, and freezing rain at the
onset of precipitation, before transitioning to light snow mid-
afternoon.
* Temperatures hovering around the 32 F mark will limit snow
accumulation on roadways, although any heavier periods of snow
may result in minor slushy accumulations.
IMPACTS...
* Drivers should be prepared for variable road conditions, with
slick spots developing especially on untreated roadways.
* Reductions in visibility to one mile or less at times.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
